  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some ways to put underline and Bold text in Facebook Chat? As previously we can do this by putting text in between underscore(_) and asterisk(*) for underline and bold text respectively?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Facebook Messenger (Facebook Chat) supports limited text formatting options. Here's how you can apply **bold** and *italic* styles to your text. Unfortunately, **underlining** text isn't natively supported in Facebook Messenger, but I'll provide some alternative suggestions below.\n\n### **1. Bold Text**\nTo make your text **bold**, enclose it within asterisks (`*`).  \n**Example:**  \n```\n*This text will be bold*\n```\n**Result:** *This text will be bold*\n\n### *2. Italic Text*\nTo italicize your text, enclose it within underscores (`_`).  \n**Example:**  \n```\n_This text will be italic_\n```\n**Result:** _This text will be italic_\n\n### **3. Strikethrough Text**\nIf you want to add a strikethrough effect, use tildes (`~`) around your text.  \n**Example:**  \n```\n~This text will be strikethrough~\n```\n**Result:** ~This text will be strikethrough~\n\n### **4. Underlined Text (Not Natively Supported)**\nFacebook Messenger does not provide a built-in way to underline text using simple formatting symbols. However, you can achieve an underlined effect through the following methods:\n\n#### **a. Using Third-Party Text Generators**\nThere are online tools that convert your text into Unicode characters that resemble underlined text. Here's how you can use them:\n\n1. **Visit a Unicode Text Generator:**\n   - Websites like [LingoJam](https://lingojam.com/UnderlineTextGenerator) or [YayText](https://yaytext.com/underline-text/) allow you to input text and convert it to various styles, including underlined.\n\n2. **Generate Underlined Text:**\n   - Enter your desired text, and the tool will provide several underlined versions.\n\n3. **Copy and Paste:**\n   - Copy the generated underlined text and paste it into your Facebook Messenger chat.\n\n**Example:**\n```\nU\u0332n\u0332d\u0332e\u0332r\u0332l\u0332i\u0332n\u0332e\u0332d\u0332 T\u0332e\u0332x\u0332t\u0332\n```\n\n> **Note:** While this method creates an underlined appearance, it's using special Unicode characters. Some recipients might find it looks different across devices or platforms, and excessive use might affect readability.\n\n#### **b. Using Emojis or Symbols**\nAs an alternative, you can use emojis or symbols before or after your text to mimic an underline effect. For example:\n\n```\n\u2796\u2796\u2796 Underlined Text \u2796\u2796\u2796\n```\n\nWhile not a true underline, it can add emphasis to your message.\n\n### **Summary**\n\n- **Bold:** `*bold*` \u2192 *bold*\n- **Italic:** `_italic_` \u2192 _italic_\n- **Strikethrough:** `~strikethrough~` \u2192 ~strikethrough~\n- **Underline:** Not supported natively; use third-party Unicode generators or symbols as alternatives.\n\nI hope this helps you format your messages effectively on Facebook Messenger!",
